The paper deals with channel estimation in multi-cell multiuser massive MIMO systems, which involves information theory (IT), networking and internet architecture (NI), systems and control (SY), multimedia (MM), and computer communication (COM). However, the focus is primarily on channel estimation, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely category. The paper also involves networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) since it deals with multi-cell multiuser systems. The paper also involves systems and control (cs.SY) since it deals with the optimization of the hybrid pilot scheme. The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) since it deals with massive MIMO systems. Finally, the paper also involves computer communication (cs.COM) since it deals with the uplink transmission of multi-cell multiuser systems.
